1
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:06,470
We began with a general idea

2
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:10,780
of what the self is,
what the soul is;

3
00:00:10,780 --> 00:00:12,618
that’s also 
in Bhagavad-gītā.

4
00:00:12,628 --> 00:00:16,418
[Mind Is the Seat of Sense Experience]

5
00:00:16,818 --> 00:00:19,369
Kṛṣṇa’s showing
in a hop, skip, and a jump

6
00:00:19,369 --> 00:00:23,199
to go from mundane world

7
00:00:23,199 --> 00:00:28,579
into the beginning
of the spiritual world.

8
00:00:28,579 --> 00:00:32,202
indriyāṇi parāṇy āhur
indriyebhyaḥ paraṁ manaḥ 
[Bg: 3.42]

9
00:00:32,202 --> 00:00:35,004
You have senses:
you can see,

10
00:00:35,004 --> 00:00:40,074
hear, taste, touch, 
smell, and feel.

11
00:00:40,074 --> 00:00:45,421
We are seeing, 
this ability to perform

12
00:00:45,421 --> 00:00:48,421
these varieties 
of sensual activities,

13
00:00:48,421 --> 00:00:54,495
[this] demonstrates 
that the senses

14
00:00:54,495 --> 00:00:58,645
are superior to the objects 
of the senses.

15
00:00:58,645 --> 00:01:01,039
So the sense, 
which can smell,

16
00:01:01,039 --> 00:01:04,481
is superior to the object 
that’s being smelled;

17
00:01:04,481 --> 00:01:07,481
what can see, etc.

18
00:01:09,181 --> 00:01:10,411
manasas tu parā buddhir 
[Bg: 3.42]

19
00:01:10,411 --> 00:01:12,111
and then he’s saying,

20
00:01:12,111 --> 00:01:15,451
indriyāṇi parāṇy āhur
indriyebhyaḥ paraṁ manaḥ—

21
00:01:15,451 --> 00:01:21,103
but superior to the senses
is the mind.

22
00:01:21,243 --> 00:01:24,377
Why? 
Because it’s the mind,

23
00:01:24,377 --> 00:01:30,037
that indulges us
with sensual capacity.

24
00:01:30,877 --> 00:01:35,317
Like there is
the common saying

25
00:01:35,317 --> 00:01:38,297
or that are synonymous:

26
00:01:38,297 --> 00:01:41,097
‘loosing your mind’ and 
‘have you lost your senses’,

27
00:01:41,097 --> 00:01:43,662
‘have lost your mind’,
‘have your lost your senses’—

28
00:01:43,662 --> 00:01:49,092
same thing, because the mind
is the seat of sense experience.

29
00:01:52,228 --> 00:02:01,098
So, like when we’re anesthetized,
we are not feeling.

30
00:02:01,110 --> 00:02:05,823
So when we are put 
into a state of unconsciousness—

31
00:02:06,373 --> 00:02:08,433
we don’t mind.

32
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:14,913
I remember once, having an operation,
in a hospital,

33
00:02:14,913 --> 00:02:21,303
and they gave me
different types of drugs,

34
00:02:21,313 --> 00:02:24,003
and the drugs are just starting
to take their effect;

35
00:02:24,003 --> 00:02:28,703
and they talk to you for a while,
to see how you're doing.

36
00:02:28,703 --> 00:02:31,462
And I was a young devotee 
at the time,

37
00:02:31,462 --> 00:02:34,732
so I thought [that] I have to preach 
at every opportunity,

38
00:02:34,732 --> 00:02:38,604
so I am preaching to them,
they are willing me into the room,

39
00:02:38,604 --> 00:02:41,123
“Oh, ye … ”, 
[Laughing]

40
00:02:41,123 --> 00:02:44,923
And then it reached the point 
where I couldn’t tell

41
00:02:44,923 --> 00:02:47,467
are they asking me questions
or am I,

42
00:02:47,467 --> 00:02:49,337
or it just some people
in my mind,

43
00:02:49,337 --> 00:02:52,028
who are asking me questions, 
or nobody;

44
00:02:52,028 --> 00:02:54,786
am I actually speaking 
or not speaking …

45
00:02:54,786 --> 00:02:58,226
It was getting heavier,
and heavier, and heavier,

46
00:02:58,246 --> 00:03:04,236
until the next thing I’ve heard
was the doctor going,

47
00:03:04,236 --> 00:03:08,737
(they are all looking over—
it’s local anesthesia),

48
00:03:08,737 --> 00:03:12,332
and the doctor’s going,
“Hammer”, [clapping] —“Hammer”,

49
00:03:12,332 --> 00:03:13,802
“Chisel”
—“Chisel” [laughing]

50
00:03:13,802 --> 00:03:16,532
and I am going,
“Hammer, chisel”

51
00:03:16,821 --> 00:03:19,971
and he put that on my head,
and he’s going,

52
00:03:20,099 --> 00:03:22,649
[Laughing]

53
00:03:23,230 --> 00:03:26,054
but at that time
I have a big smile on my …

54
00:03:26,054 --> 00:03:31,302
“Hammer, chisel. Ha-ha!”
[Laughing]

55
00:03:31,302 --> 00:03:33,299
—“Hammer away!”

56
00:03:35,119 --> 00:03:37,269
The last time
I went to the hospital,

57
00:03:37,490 --> 00:03:40,751
it was in Marin County,

58
00:03:40,751 --> 00:03:45,831
which is kind of like 
this California Wonderland,

59
00:03:45,831 --> 00:03:50,381
and it’s like 
going to a four-star hotel,

60
00:03:50,381 --> 00:03:52,951
and they treat you 
very nicely,

61
00:03:52,951 --> 00:03:55,391
it seems like you 
are the only person in the hospital,

62
00:03:55,391 --> 00:03:58,140
(you don’t even see other people,
except them)

63
00:03:58,140 --> 00:04:01,499
and they willed me into the room
and then they started giving me

64
00:04:01,499 --> 00:04:06,777
that anesthesia,
but this is like [breathing in]

65
00:04:06,777 --> 00:04:11,597
it’s like a very nice aroma, 
fragrant,

66
00:04:11,597 --> 00:04:15,587
this is like new age anesthesia;
[Laughing]

67
00:04:15,595 --> 00:04:20,325
really like sweet, tasty, 
[breathing in] smelling really nice,

68
00:04:20,325 --> 00:04:23,265
like as good,
as the best flowers.

69
00:04:23,265 --> 00:04:24,875
[breathing in] 
I’m smelling this

70
00:04:24,875 --> 00:04:26,945
and they are talking
to me to see also

71
00:04:26,945 --> 00:04:30,405
if it will …
if it’s taking effect,

72
00:04:30,405 --> 00:04:34,435
and then they also
have a poster on the ceiling,

73
00:04:34,435 --> 00:04:37,435
and there is 
this beautiful nature scene;

74
00:04:37,435 --> 00:04:41,089
and I made some jokes about it,
and I said,

75
00:04:41,089 --> 00:04:47,269
“I don’t feel the anesthesia
taking effect, I’m a little worried.”

76
00:04:47,269 --> 00:04:51,906
And they’re saying,
“Oh-oh, ok, this ok.”

77
00:04:51,906 --> 00:04:55,286
And then the next thing 
I noticed

78
00:04:55,286 --> 00:04:58,286
(because I made a joke 
about the poster),

79
00:04:58,286 --> 00:05:02,688
the poster was gone,
and I said, “I was just kidding,

80
00:05:02,688 --> 00:05:06,268
you can leave the poster!”
(’cause I made some joke about it)

81
00:05:06,268 --> 00:05:09,909
You can put your poster back—
it was only a joke,

82
00:05:09,909 --> 00:05:13,123
but it was four hours later,
[Laughing]

83
00:05:13,123 --> 00:05:16,742
and I was in a different room—
that’s why there is no poster,

84
00:05:16,742 --> 00:05:18,487
[Laughing]

85
00:05:18,487 --> 00:05:20,857
and then this nurse,
she comes over, and she says,

86
00:05:20,857 --> 00:05:27,407
“I want you to take this pill, 
and this cracker”,

87
00:05:27,407 --> 00:05:30,871
and then she sat down, 
and when she was eating a cracker,

88
00:05:30,871 --> 00:05:32,831
and I said,
“You can have a cracker,

89
00:05:32,831 --> 00:05:35,711
but you can’t have a pill.” 
[Laughing]

90
00:05:35,711 --> 00:05:38,931
And she was like, “Oh, 
this is gonna be a good one.“

91
00:05:38,931 --> 00:05:41,691
[Laughing]

92
00:05:41,991 --> 00:05:44,277
and then there is this machine,
with what, you know,

93
00:05:44,277 --> 00:05:46,974
blood pressure and
all these different things,

94
00:05:46,974 --> 00:05:50,434
and I said,
“I’d like to see it.”

95
00:05:51,074 --> 00:05:53,387
And she said ‘ok’, 
she turned it around,

96
00:05:53,387 --> 00:05:57,187
so I could see
all this digital read-out,

97
00:05:57,187 --> 00:06:01,211
and she said, “You let me know
if something goes wrong.

98
00:06:01,211 --> 00:06:08,791
[Laughing]

99
00:06:08,807 --> 00:06:14,147
So anyway, I could understand,
what happened in those four hours,

100
00:06:14,148 --> 00:06:18,311
because my mind …
I’ve been anesthetized

101
00:06:18,311 --> 00:06:22,198
at point where no seeing, 
hearing, tasting, smelling …

102
00:06:22,198 --> 00:06:25,688
everything was turned off,

103
00:06:26,108 --> 00:06:29,228
so the mind is the seat 
of sense experience.

